m\geq0,m,n\in\mathbb{N}
\int_0^{\frac{1}{2}}\cot(\pi x)\sin(2\pi nx)\cos(2\pi mx)\,dx=\begin{cases}0&m>n\\\frac{1}{4}&m=n\\\frac{1}{2}&m<n\end{cases}
\int_0^{1/2}\cot(\pi x)\sin(2\pi nx)\cos(2\pi nx)dx = \frac{1}{2}\int_0^{1/2}\cot(\pi x)\sin(4\pi nx)dx
\frac{1}{2}\int_0^{1/2}\cot(\pi x)\sin(4\pi nx)dx = \frac{1}{2}\int_0^{1/2}\cos(\pi x)dx = \frac{1}{2}\int_0^{1/2}dx = \frac{1}{4}
\sin(4\pi nx)
